  <static seed="1311" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalFunctions/reduceRationalFunction40.pg">
    <statement><p>Simplify the function formula, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ h(x) = {\frac{2x^{3}+5x^{2}}{2x^{3}+9x^{2}+10x}} }</m></p>
<p>Reduced <m>h(x)=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{x}{x+2}, x\ne -2.5\hbox{ and }x\ne 0</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cancel common factors.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   h(x) \amp = {\frac{2x^{3}+5x^{2}}{2x^{3}+9x^{2}+10x}} \\
                 \amp = \frac{{x^{2}\mathopen{}\left(2x+5\right)}}{{x\mathopen{}\left(2x^{2}+9x+10\right)}} \\
                 \amp = \frac{{x^{2}\mathopen{}\left(2x+5\right)}}{{x\mathopen{}\left(2x+5\right)\mathopen{}\left(x+2\right)}} \\
                 \amp = {\frac{x}{x+2}, x\ne -2.5\hbox{ and }x\ne 0}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>The expression <m>x(2x+5)</m> was canceled. To find what values would cause the crossed out expression to be <m>0</m>, we solve the equation:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   x(2x+5) \amp = 0 \\
   x = 0 \amp \text{ or } 2x+5=0 \\
   x = 0 \amp \text{ or } 2x=-5 \\
   x = 0 \amp \text{ or } x= {-{\frac{5}{2}}} \\
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>The domain condition lost during the reduction is <m>x \ne {-{\frac{5}{2}}\; and \;0}</m>.</p>
</solution>
